1
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:09,240
MAN: "But who is this creature
with terrible claws,

2
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:13,040
"and terrible teeth in his terrible jaws?"

3
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:15,800
Go on, your bit.

4
00:00:17,880 --> 00:00:21,400
"He, he has..." Go on!

5
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:24,480
I can't do it, Dad.
I can listen to books, anyway.

6
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:28,600
I know it doesn't come easy, son,
but you've got to keep at it, all right?

7
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:30,560
You're not on your own with this.

8
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:33,160
Mo, you'll be late for your shift.

9
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:35,160
Oh, you're right!

10
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,360
Sorry, EL, got to go.

11
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:39,640
Now, who loves you more than me?

12
00:00:39,720 --> 00:00:42,520
- No-one.
- Stop saying that!

13
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:44,600
Mwah!

14
00:00:58,640 --> 00:01:01,240
COMPUTER: Approaching stage four,
target drilling depth.

15
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:04,520
Stage four target drill depth
scheduled in five,

16
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,880
four, three, two, one.

17
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:09,600
Stage four target drill
depth achieved.

18
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:12,800
- Oh!
- Drill depth now 217 kilometres.

19
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:17,880
Hi. Nasreen here, just to let you know
we have just hit our new target!

20
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:19,600
21 kilometres, folks!

21
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:22,120
Further than anyone's ever
drilled into the Earth.

22
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:25,600
Thanks for your amazing work.
Have a great weekend!

23
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:27,760
Onwards and downwards.

24
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:30,680
How much further
do you think we can we go, Mack?

25
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,720
Into the unknown!

26
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:36,120
- Exciting, isn't it?
- Yeah.

27
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,840
Aye, aye! Stop that!
The real worker's here now!

28
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:39,960
- Evening, Mo!
- 21k?

29
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:41,880
Whoo-hoo!

30
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:44,880
You wanted to grab all the glory
before I come on shift!

31
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:48,240
Right, off you go, get out,
my gaff for the night.

32
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,400
Brilliant.

33
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:10,600
(RATTLING)

34
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,040
(SWITCH CLICKS ON AND OFF)

35
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:15,160
That is mad.

36
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:38,080
Oh!

37
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:39,720
Please...

38
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:48,000
Ahh!

39
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,080
Argh!

40
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:36,440
Behold...Rio!

41
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,640
- Nuh-uh.
- Not really getting

42
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,840
- the sunshine carnival vibe.
- No!

43
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:47,680
Ooh, feel that, though, what's that?

44
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,160
(LOW RUMBLING)

45
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:52,120
Ground feels strange...

46
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:56,560
Just me. Wait...

47
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:59,000
- That's weird.
- RORY: What's weird?

48
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:01,920
Doctor, stop trying to distract us.
We're in the wrong place.

49
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,840
Doctor, it's freezing
and I've dressed for Rio.

50
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:07,480
We are not stopping here.

51
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:10,280
Doctor! Are you listening to me?
It's a graveyard!

52
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:13,160
- You promised me a beach.
- Blue grass.

53
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,640
Patches of it
all around the graveyard.

54
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:20,880
So, Earth, 2020-ish,
ten years in your future,

55
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:24,280
wrong continent for Rio, I'll admit,
but it's not a massive overshoot.

56
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,160
Why are those people waving at us?

57
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,800
Can't be.

58
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,640
It is!

59
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:40,360
- It's you two.
- RORY: No.

60
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:43,040
We're here.
How can we be up there?!

61
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:47,200
Ten years in your future.
Come to relive past glories, I'd imagine.

62
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:49,840
Humans, you're so nostalgic.

63
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:52,640
We're still together in ten years?

64
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,240
No need to sound so surprised!

65
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:55,960
Hey, let's go and talk to them!

66
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:58,480
We can say hi to Future Us!
How cool is that?

67
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,280
No, best not, really best not.

68
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:04,560
These things get complicated
very quickly, and... Oh, look!

69
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:07,040
Big mining thing.

70
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:09,840
Oh, I love a big mining thing.

71
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:11,520
See, way better than Rio!

72
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,680
Rio doesn't have a big mining thing.

73
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:18,120
- We're not going to have a look, are we?
- Let's go and have a look!

74
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:21,080
- Come on, let's see what they're doing.
- If he can't get us to Rio,

75
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,600
how's he ever going to get us back home?

76
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,640
Did you not see, over there?
It all works out fine.

77
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:27,680
After everything we've seen,
we just drop back into our old lives,

78
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:29,320
the nurse and the kissogram?

79
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:33,120
- I guess. He's getting away.
- Hang on.

80
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,040
What are you doing with that?

81
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:37,400
Engagement ring!
I thought you liked me wearing it.

82
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:42,840
Amy! You could lose it!
Cost...a lot of money, that!

83
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,920
Hm.

84
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,080
Spoilsport.

85
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:50,080
- Go on. I'IL catch you both up.
- Doctor!

86
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:57,520
TONY: The drill's shut down!
There's no sign of Mo.

87
00:06:57,600 --> 00:07:00,840
Nobody's been in or out of
the perimeter between last night...

88
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,240
and...now. What's that?

89
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:05,920
That wasn't there last night.
How the hell did that get there?

90
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,560
I don't know.

91
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:27,640
Well, that was quick!

92
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:30,560
- Was it?
- It's great that you came.

93
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,920
Bit retro.
What is it, portable crime lab?

94
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,360
Oh. Er, sort of.

95
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:39,160
Ambrose Northover.
I was the one who called.

96
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:43,560
I run the meals on wheels for
the whole valley. This is my son, Elliot.

97
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,760
Where's your uniform?

98
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:47,080
Don't be cheeky, Elliot,
he's plain clothes.

99
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:50,360
CID, is it? Anyway, it's over here.

100
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,920
Um... OK...

101
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,600
"Restricted access".

102
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:06,400
"No unauthorised personnel”. Hm.

103
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:12,160
- That is breaking and entering.
- What did I break?!

104
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:14,360
Sonicing and entering,
totally different.

105
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:23,040
Come on, then.

106
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,000
You're sure Rory'll catch us up?

107
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:30,440
It's a family plot, see.
My aunt Gladys died six years ago.

108
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:33,280
Her husband, Alun,
died a few weeks back.

109
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:35,600
He lived in the house two doors down.

110
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:37,520
There's not many of us left up here now.

111
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:41,160
Mum, he doesn't care about that!
He wants to know about the dead bodies.

112
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:43,800
Yes. Sorry.

113
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:48,600
Well, they always wanted to be buried
in the same plot, together.

114
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:53,120
But when we went to bury Uncle Alun,
Gladys wasn't there. Gone.

115
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:56,760
Body, coffin, everything.

116
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,000
What?

117
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:03,760
The mad thing is, on the surface,
the grave was untouched.

118
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:06,440
No signs of it having been messed with.

119
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:09,680
I'm sorry, I don't understand.

120
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:13,040
Nobody has touched the grave
since my aunt was buried.

121
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:16,040
But when they dug it open,
the body was gone.

122
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:18,160
How is that possible?

123
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,200
What about now, can you feel it now?

124
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:26,840
Honestly, I've got no idea
what you're on about.

125
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,560
The ground doesn't feel like it should.

126
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,960
It's ten years in the future,

127
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:34,520
maybe how this ground feels
is how it always feels.

128
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:36,280
Good thought, but no. It doesn't.

129
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:38,120
- (WHIRRING)
- Hear that? Drill in start-up mode.

130
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:42,440
After-waves of a recent
seismological shift and blue grass.

131
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:47,680
Oh, please! Have you
always been this disgusting?

132
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:51,520
No, that's recent. What's in...

133
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:54,240
here?

134
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,640
- Hello!
- Who are you?

135
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:59,120
What are you doing here?
And what are you wearing?

136
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,840
I dressed for Rio!

137
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:05,000
Ministry of Drills, Earth and Science.
New Ministry, quite big, just merged,

138
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:09,160
a lot of responsibility, don't like
to talk about it. What are you doing?

139
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,400
None of your business.

140
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:15,160
Where are you getting
these readings from?

141
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:19,680
- Under the soil.
- The drill's up and running again.

142
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:21,840
What's going on?
Who are these people?

143
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:24,160
Amy, the Doctor.
We're not staying, are we, Doctor?!

144
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:26,680
Why's there a big patch of earth
in the middle of your floor?

145
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:29,240
We don't know,
it just appeared overnight.

146
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:34,440
Good, right, you all need
to get out of here very fast.

147
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,200
NASREEN: Why?

148
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,560
- What's your name?
- Nasreen Chaudhry.

149
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,920
Look at the screens, Nasreen,
look at your readings.

150
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,080
- It's moving.
- Hey, that's specialised equipment!

151
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:44,360
- Get away from it.
- What is?

152
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:49,240
Doctor, this steam,
is that a good thing?

153
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:54,280
Shouldn't think so. It's shifting
when it shouldn't be shifting.

154
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,200
What shouldn't?

155
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:02,760
The ground, the soil,
the earth, moving, but how? Why?

156
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,320
- AMY: Earthquake?
- TONY: What's going on?

157
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:08,400
Doubt it. Cos it's only happening
under this room.

158
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:17,520
It knows we're here.
The ground's attacking us.

159
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:20,840
- That...that's not possible!
- Under the circumstances, I'd suggest...

160
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,320
run!

161
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,280
- Tony!
- Stay back, Amy!

162
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,720
Stay away from the earth!

163
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,840
It's OK.

164
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,960
- It's pulling me down!
- Amy!

165
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:41,400
Doctor, help me, something's got me!

166
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:42,960
Take my hand!

167
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:45,200
Doctor, the ground's got my legs.

168
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,920
- I've got you.
- OK.

169
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:52,360
- Don't let go.
- Never.

170
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,400
Doctor, what is it?
Why is it doing this?

171
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:57,640
Stay calm,
keep hold of my hand, don't let go.

172
00:11:57,720 --> 00:12:02,040
Your drill, shut it down! Go! Now!

173
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,680
- Can you get me out?
- Amy, try and stay calm.

174
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,440
If you struggle, it'll make things worse.
Keep hold of my hand.

175
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:11,400
Shut down all drilling activity
as quick as you can.

176
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,200
TONY: Reducing main unit power.

177
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,280
I'm not going to let you go.

178
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:21,600
Doctor, it's pulling me down,
something's pulling me!

179
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:22,760
Stay calm.

180
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:26,880
Hold on, if they can just
shut down the drill...

181
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:30,200
- I can't hold on!
- NASREEN: Tony, we've got to be faster!

182
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:32,960
I'm doing my best!

183
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:35,040
Come on, shut down!

184
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,160
What's pulling me?
What is under the earth?

185
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:40,360
I don't want to suffocate under there.

186
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,720
Amy, concentrate.

187
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:45,200
Don't you give up!

188
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:48,120
- Tell Rory...
- No.

189
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,200
Amy!

190
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:56,880
Amy, no! No! No!

191
00:12:56,960 --> 00:13:00,560
No! No! No!

192
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:02,120
No.

193
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:05,080
No!

194
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:08,840
No. No. No.

195
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:10,040
No!

196
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,920
Where is she?

197
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:29,240
She's gone. The ground took her.

198
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:39,880
- Do you want sugar?
- Oh... Sorry?

199
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:42,400
In your tea. Mum's asking.

200
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:45,200
No. Just white, thanks.

201
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:47,840
There's only one explanation,
as far as I can see.

202
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:50,440
- What's that, then?
- The graves eat people.

203
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:53,040
Devour them whole, leaving no trace.

204
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:56,360
- Not sure about that.
- They didn't steal the body from above.

205
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,720
They couldn't have got in from the sides.

206
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:01,720
Only other thing is,
they get in from underneath.

207
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,440
Not very likely, though.

208
00:14:03,520 --> 00:14:05,600
"When you've eliminated
the impossible,

209
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:08,800
"whatever remains, however improbable,
must be the truth."”

210
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:09,800
Sorry?

211
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,280
Sherlock Holmes.

212
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:12,920
Got the audio book.

213
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:17,400
The graves round here eat people.

214
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:24,520
(SHIVERS)

215
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:27,640
Is that what happened to Mo?
Are they dead?

216
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:31,200
It's not quicksand.

217
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:34,560
She didn't just sink -
something pulled her in, it wanted her.

218
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:36,480
The ground wanted her?

219
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:38,960
You said the ground was dormant,

220
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:41,600
just a patch of earth,
when you first saw it this morning.

221
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:45,080
And the drill had been stopped.

222
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,640
That's right.

223
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:49,760
But when you re-started the drill,
the ground fought back.

224
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:53,720
So, what, the ground wants
to stop us drilling?!

225
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:56,080
NASREEN: Doctor, that is ridiculous.

226
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:57,800
(HIGH-PITCHED WHINING)

227
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:58,720
(RUMBLING)

228
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:01,280
I'm not saying that, and it's not
ridiculous, I just don't think it's right.

229
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:03,320
Oh! Of course!

230
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:05,200
Ha! It's bio-programming!

231
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,760
What?!

232
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:10,520
Bio-programming! Oh, clever.

233
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,320
You use bio-signals to resonate

234
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:14,640
the internal molecular structure
of natural objects.

235
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:18,280
It's mainly used in engineering
and construction, mostly jungle planets,

236
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:21,600
but that's way in the future,
and not here. What's it doing here?

237
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:23,520
Sorry, did you just say "jungle planets"?

238
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,960
You're not making any sense, man!

239
00:15:26,040 --> 00:15:29,080
'Souse me, I'm making perfect sense,
you're just not keeping up.

240
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:34,520
The earth, the ground beneath our feet,
was bio-programmed to attack.

241
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,960
Yeah, even if that were possible,
which, by the way, it's not, why?

242
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,560
Stop you drilling. OK, so we find
what's doing the bio-programming,

243
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:42,800
we can find Amy, we can get her back.
Ssh, ssh, ssh!

244
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,680
Have I gone mad? I've gone mad!

245
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:47,520
- Doctor...
- Ssh, ssh! Silence! Absolute silence!

246
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,880
- You stopped the drill, right?
- Yes.

247
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,440
And you've only got the one drill?

248
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:02,680
- Yes.
- You're sure about that?

249
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:03,960
Yes!

250
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:13,000
- (WHIRRING)
- So, if you shut the drill down...

251
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:15,800
why can I still hear drilling?

252
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,920
- It's under the ground.
- That's not possible.

253
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:27,440
- (HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING)
- Oh, no, what are you doing?!

254
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:30,240
Hacking into your records.
Probe reports, samples, sensors, good,

255
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:33,480
just unite the data, make it all
one big conversation, let's have a look.

256
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:36,720
So. We are here
and this is your drill hole.

257
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:39,040
21.009 kilometres.

258
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,840
Well done!

259
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,840
Thank you. It's taken us a long time.

260
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,520
Why here, though? Why drill on this site?

261
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:49,400
We found patches of grass
in this area, containing trace minerals

262
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:51,840
unseen in this country for...
20 million years.

263
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:54,600
The blue grass? Oh, Nasreen,

264
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:57,560
those trace minerals weren't
X marking the spot, saying "dig here".

265
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:59,200
They were a warning. "Stay away."

266
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:01,920
Cos while you've been
drilling down...

267
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:06,120
...somebody else has been drilling up.

268
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:10,840
Oh...beautiful.

269
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,200
Network of tunnels all the way down.

270
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,360
No, no, we've surveyed that area.

271
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:17,440
You only saw what you went looking for.

272
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:20,040
- (REGULAR BLEEPING)
- Oh...what...what are they?

273
00:17:20,120 --> 00:17:21,840
DOCTOR: Heat signals.

274
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:24,880
Wait. Dual readings, hot and cold,
doesn't make sense.

275
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:27,040
And now they're moving.

276
00:17:27,120 --> 00:17:29,200
Fast. How many people live nearby?

277
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:30,800
Just my daughter and her family.

278
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,360
The rest of the staff travel in.

279
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:35,160
Grab this equipment and follow me.

280
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:36,920
Why? What are we doing?

281
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,320
That noise isn't a drill.

282
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:43,840
It's transport. Three of them, 30km down,
rate of speed looks about 150km an hour.

283
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:47,200
Should be here in...
ooh, quite soon...

284
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:48,680
12 minutes.

285
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:53,880
Whatever bio-programmed
the earth is on its way up. Now.

286
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:00,640
How can something be coming up when
there's only the Earth's crust down there?

287
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:02,000
You saw the readings!

288
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:04,840
Who are you, anyway?
How can you know all this?

289
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:07,640
- (STRAFING NOISES)
- Whoa!

290
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:09,600
Did you see that?

291
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:12,960
No, no, no!

292
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:23,120
(ELECTRONIC FIZZLING)

293
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:31,160
Energy signal originating from
under the earth. We're trapped.

294
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:35,520
Doctor, something weird's going on here,
the graves are eating people.

295
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,680
Not now, Rory!

296
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:39,800
Energy barricade.
Invisible to the naked eye.

297
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:42,600
We can't get out and no-one
from the outside world can get in.

298
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,600
What?

299
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:46,360
OK, what about the TARDIS?

300
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:48,200
The what?

301
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:50,800
Er, no, those energy patterns
would play havoc with the circuits.

302
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:54,440
With a bit of time, maybe, but we've
only got nine and a half minutes.

303
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:56,960
Nine and a half minutes to what?

304
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:59,960
We're trapped. And something's
burrowing towards the surface.

305
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:03,160
Where's Amy?

306
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:07,640
Get everyone inside the church.

307
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:10,480
Rory, I'UL get her back.

308
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:12,720
What do you mean, "get her back"?
Where's she gone?

309
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:14,160
She was taken.

310
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:16,120
Into the earth.

311
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:18,080
How?

312
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,520
Why didn't you stop it?

313
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:22,480
- I tried. I promise, I tried.
- Well, you should've tried harder!

314
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:25,400
I'L find Amy.
I'll keep you all safe. I promise.

315
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:27,640
Come on, please.

316
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:29,560
I need you alongside me.

317
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,600
(ELECTRONIC FIZZLING)

318
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,760
(SHE TAKES A BREATH)

319
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:51,720
(STEADY BLEEPING)

320
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:59,560
Where's Mo? Is he with you?

321
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:04,400
This flaming door, always sticking!
I thought you were having it fixed!

322
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,360
Dad!

323
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:08,200
Something's happened to him, hasn't it?

324
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:13,720
So we can't get out,
we can't contact anyone,

325
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:18,040
and something, the something that took my
husband, is coming up through the earth.

326
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:20,040
Yes. If we move quickly enough,
we can be ready.

327
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:23,560
No, stop. This has gone far enough.
I mean, what is this?

328
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:26,120
- He's telling the truth, love.
- Come on!

329
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:30,200
It's not the first time we've had no
phone signals. Reception's always rubbish.

330
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:32,960
Look, Ambrose, we saw
the Doctor's friend get taken, OK?

331
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:34,880
You saw the lightning in the sky.

332
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:37,480
I have seen the impossible today,

333
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:40,440
and the only person who's made
any sense of it, for me, is the Doctor.

334
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:42,920
- Him?!
- Me!

335
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,320
Can you get my dad back?

336
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:52,960
Yes.

337
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:54,640
But I need you to trust me

338
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:57,120
and do exactly as I say
from this second onwards,

339
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:59,040
because we're running out of time.

340
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,160
So tell us what to do.

341
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:08,080
Thank you. We have eight minutes
to set up a line of defence.

342
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,320
Bring me every phone,

343
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:12,600
every camera, every piece of recording
or transmitting equipment you can find.

344
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:18,000
Every burglar alarm, every movement
sensor, every security light!

345
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:21,000
I want the whole area
covered with sensors.

346
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:25,160
(HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING)

347
00:21:25,240 --> 00:21:27,400
Right, guys, we need to be ready
for whatever's coming up.

348
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:30,520
I need a map of the village,
marking where the cameras are going.

349
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,360
I can't do the words. I'm dyslexic.

350
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:34,760
Oh, that's all right,
I can't make a decent meringue.

351
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:37,200
Draw like your life depends on it, Elliot.

352
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,240
6 minutes 40.

353
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,840
(BLEEPING)

354
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:55,680
Works in quadrants, every movement
sensor and trip light we've got.

355
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:57,840
If anything moves, we'll know.

356
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,400
Good lad!

357
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:07,240
AMBROSE: Oi! What are you doing?!

358
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:08,680
Resources!

359
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:12,320
Every little helps! Meals on wheels.

360
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:16,000
What've you got here, then? Warmer
in the front, refrigerated in the back.

361
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:18,720
Bit chilly for a hideout, mind.

362
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:22,240
- What are those?
- Like you say, every little helps.

363
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:25,040
No! No weapons.
It's not the way I do things.

364
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:27,160
Well, you said we're supposed
to be defending ourselves.

365
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:30,480
Oh, Ambrose, you're better than this.
I'm asking nicely.

366
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:32,560
Put them away.

367
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:50,080
Look at that! Perfect!

368
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:53,240
Dyslexia never stopped Da Vinci
or Einstein, it's not stopping you.

369
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:55,440
I don't understand
what you're going to do.

370
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:58,720
Two-phase plan. First, the sensors and
cameras tell us when something arrives.

371
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,400
Second, if something does arrive,

372
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:03,440
I use this to send a sonic pulse
through that network of devices,

373
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:06,440
a pulse which would temporarily
incapacitate most things in the universe.

374
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:08,280
Knock 'em out. Cool.

375
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:13,960
- Lovely place to grow up, round here.
- Suppose.

376
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:17,800
I want to live in a city one day.
Soon as I'm old enough, I'll be off.

377
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:20,960
- I was the same, where I grew up.
- Did you get away?

378
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:23,320
- Yeah.
- Do you ever miss it?

379
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:27,960
So much.

380
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,280
Is it monsters coming?

381
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:35,480
Have you met monsters before?

382
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:38,720
- Yeah.
- You scared of them?

383
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:40,440
No. They're scared of me.

384
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:43,240
Will you really get my dad back?

385
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:45,120
No question.

386
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:48,760
I left my headphones at home.

387
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:03,040
- How are you doing?
- It's getting darker.

388
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:05,640
How can it be getting dark so quickly?

389
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:08,600
Shutting out light within the barricade.
Trying to isolate us in the dark.

390
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,120
Which means...

391
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,640
(RUMBLING)

392
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:14,440
...it's here.

393
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:18,320
They're close to the surface now.

394
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:20,360
(STEADY BLEEPING)

395
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:28,560
- Tony!
- Like you didn't know.

396
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:41,120
(BLEEPING STOPS)

397
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:44,320
I can't open it! It keeps sticking!
The wood's warped.

398
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:47,200
- Any time you want to help(!)
- Can't you sonic it?

399
00:24:47,280 --> 00:24:49,400
- It doesn't do wood.
- That is rubbish.

400
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:51,040
Oi! Don't diss the sonic!

401
00:24:58,040 --> 00:25:00,680
See if we can get a fix.

402
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,680
(ELECTRONIC SCRAMBLING)

403
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:25,200
- No power.
- It's deliberate.

404
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:27,520
What do we do now?

405
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:31,680
Nothing. We've got nothing! They sent
an energy surge to wreck our systems.

406
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:34,240
Is everyone OK? Is anyone hurt?

407
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,280
- Fine.
- All good.

408
00:25:35,360 --> 00:25:36,280
Me too.

409
00:25:36,360 --> 00:25:38,880
(RUMBLING)

410
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:42,360
(AMBROSE GASPS)

411
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:45,120
Doctor...what was that?

412
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,760
TONY: Like the holes at the drill station.

413
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:48,240
AMBROSE: Is this how they happened?

414
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:54,000
It's coming through
the final layer of earth.

415
00:25:54,080 --> 00:25:55,520
What is?

416
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:59,680
(SILENCE)

417
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:01,520
Banging's stopped.

418
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:06,840
Where's Elliot?

419
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:08,720
Has...has anyone seen Elliot?

420
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:12,720
Did he come in?
was he in when the door was shut?

421
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:14,680
Who counted him back in?

422
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:16,520
Who saw him last?

423
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:20,640
I did.

424
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:24,200
Where is he?

425
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:28,040
He said he was going to get headphones.

426
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:30,040
And you let him go?!

427
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:33,200
He was out there on his own?!

428
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:45,160
(HE PANTS)

429
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:53,600
(GROWLING)

430
00:26:57,040 --> 00:27:00,680
Mum! Grandpa Tony! Let me in!

431
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:03,200
- Elliot!
- Let me in!

432
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:04,920
He's out there! Help me!

433
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,960
Open the door!

434
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:08,840
Mum! There's something out here!

435
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:12,400
Push, Elliot!
Push, Elliot, give it a shove!

436
00:27:12,480 --> 00:27:15,280
] - Mum!
Push! Hurry up!

437
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:21,120
(SNARLING)

438
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:24,960
Mum...

439
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:28,400
- TONY: Come on!
- AMBROSE: Elliot!

440
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:31,800
Where is he?!

441
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:35,280
He was here!

442
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:39,080
He was here! Elliot!

443
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:42,000
- Ambrose, don't go running off!
- Ambrose!

444
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:44,560
Elliot! It's Mum!

445
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,760
(BLEEPING)

446
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:57,680
No-0-0-0-0-0!

447
00:28:01,760 --> 00:28:04,400
Aaargh! Get off me!

448
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:10,640
(SNARLING)

449
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:12,320
Argh!

450
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:15,920
- Dad! Dad!
- DOCTOR: What happened?

451
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:18,040
My dad's hurt!

452
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:20,200
Get him into the church now!

453
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:21,480
Elliot's gone!

454
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:23,920
They've killed him, haven't they?

455
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,680
I don't think so.

456
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:28,960
They've taken three people, when
they could've just killed them up here.

457
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:32,640
There's still hope, Ambrose.
There is always hope.

458
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:34,360
Then why have they taken him?

459
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,080
I don't know.

460
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:39,680
I'LL find Elliot, I promise.
But first I've got to stop this attack.

461
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:42,600
Please, get inside the church.

462
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:49,080
- Come on, Dad. Come on.
- So, what now?

463
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:12,200
(DISTANT HISSING)

464
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,920
Cold blood.

465
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:28,920
(SING-SONG VOICE) I know who they are.

466
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:34,400
(HE WHISTLES)

467
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:41,160
(SNARLING)

468
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:48,560
(SCREAMING)

469
00:29:57,320 --> 00:30:00,960
We got it! Defending the planet
with meals on wheels!

470
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:04,120
- (RUMBLING)
- What...what was that?

471
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:06,040
Sounds like they're leaving.

472
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:07,720
Without this one?

473
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:11,520
RORY: Looks like we scared them off.

474
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:13,320
I don't think so.

475
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:17,960
Now both sides have hostages.

476
00:30:30,560 --> 00:30:31,480
Let me out.

477
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:34,680
Can anybody hear me?
I'm alive in here!

478
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:36,640
Let me out!

479
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:40,400
I know you're out there!

480
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:44,040
My name is Amy Pond, and you'd better
get me the hell out of here

481
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:47,120
or so help me,
I'm going to kick your backside!

482
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:50,800
Please?

483
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:53,440
Shh!

484
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:55,280
Did you just shush me?

485
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:58,760
Did you just shush...me?!

486
00:30:58,840 --> 00:31:00,920
No, no, no, don't do that. No gas.

487
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:02,320
No gas!

488
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:05,200
(SHE SPLUTTERS)

489
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:12,320
So, I think I've met
these creatures before.

490
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:14,760
Different branch of the species, mind,
but all the same...

491
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:16,560
Let's see if our friend's thawed out.

492
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:19,480
- Are you sure? By yourself?
- Very sure.

493
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:20,920
But the sting...

494
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,640
Venom gland takes
at least 24 hours to recharge.

495
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:25,120
Am I right?

496
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:26,840
(HEAVY BREATHING)

497
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:29,240
I know what I'm doing.

498
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:30,800
I'll be fine.

499
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,520
I'm the Doctor.

500
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:48,520
I've come to talk.

501
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:51,640
I'm going to remove your mask.

502
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:01,040
(HEAVY BREATHING)

503
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:12,080
You are beautiful.

504
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:19,080
Remnant of a bygone age on Planet Earth.

505
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:22,880
And by the way, lovely mode of travel!

506
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:26,800
Geothermal currents, projecting you up
through a network of tunnels.

507
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:28,440
Gorgeous! Mind if I sit?

508
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:30,760
Now.

509
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:32,600
Your people...

510
00:32:32,680 --> 00:32:36,000
have a friend of mine.

511
00:32:40,680 --> 00:32:42,440
I want her back.

512
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:45,880
Why did you come to the surface?

513
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:50,120
What do you want?

514
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:55,440
Oh, I do hate a monologue.
Give us a bit back. How many are you?

515
00:32:56,520 --> 00:32:58,640
I'm the last of my species.

516
00:32:58,720 --> 00:32:59,920
Really?

517
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:05,120
No. "Last of the species”,
the Klempari Defence. Ha!

518
00:33:05,200 --> 00:33:09,400
As an interrogation defence,
it's a bit old hat, I'm afraid.

519
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:11,960
I'm the last of my species.

520
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:14,080
No. You're really not.

521
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:18,960
Because I'm the last of my species
and I know how it sits in a heart.

522
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:20,720
So don't insult me.

523
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:25,440
Let's start again.

524
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:27,840
Tell me your name.

525
00:33:30,560 --> 00:33:31,520
Alaya.

526
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:35,200
How long has your tribe been
sleeping under the earth, Alaya?

527
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,480
It's not difficult to work out.

528
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:41,120
You're 300 million years
out of your comfort zone.

529
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:43,160
Question is, what woke you now?

530
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:45,000
We were attacked.

531
00:33:46,040 --> 00:33:47,920
The drill.

532
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:51,360
Our sensors detected a threat
to our life support systems.

533
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:54,080
The warrior class was activated
to prevent the assault.

534
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:57,680
We will wipe the vermin from
the surface and reclaim our planet.

535
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:59,560
Do we have to say "vermin"?

536
00:33:59,640 --> 00:34:01,160
They're really very nice.

537
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:02,920
- Primitive apes.
- Extraordinary species.

538
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:05,280
You attack them,
they'll fight back. But...

539
00:34:05,360 --> 00:34:07,920
there's a peace to be brokered here.

540
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,720
I can help you with that.

541
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:11,280
This land is ours.

542
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:13,200
We lived here long before the apes.

543
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:16,800
Doesn't give you
automatic rights to it now, I'm afraid.

544
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:20,200
- Humans won't give up the planet.
- So we destroy them.

545
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:22,400
- You underestimate them.
- You underestimate us!

546
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:24,840
One tribe of Homo reptilia
against six billion humans?

547
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:26,280
You've got your work cut out.

548
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:31,240
We did not initiate combat.
But we can still win.

549
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:33,720
Tell me where my friend is.

550
00:34:34,720 --> 00:34:37,000
Give us back the people who were taken.

551
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:38,520
No.

552
00:34:47,520 --> 00:34:50,160
I'm not going to let you
provoke a war, Alaya.

553
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:54,880
There'll be no battle here today.

554
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:57,840
The fire of war is already lit.
A massacre is due.

555
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,840
Not while I'm here.

556
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:06,240
I'll gladly die for my cause.
What will you sacrifice for yours?

557
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,880
You're going to what?!

558
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:16,520
I'm going to go down
below the surface,

559
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:19,520
to find the rest of the tribe,
to talk to them.

560
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:22,640
You're going to negotiate
with these aliens?

561
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:26,120
They're not aliens!
They're Earth...liens.

562
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:30,880
Once known as the Silurian race,
or, some would argue, Eocenes,

563
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:33,000
or Homo reptilia.

564
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:35,080
Not monsters, not evil.

565
00:35:35,160 --> 00:35:37,960
Well...only as evil as you are.

566
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:41,560
The previous owners
of the planet, that's all.

567
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:45,640
Look...from their point of view,
you're the invaders.

568
00:35:45,720 --> 00:35:48,560
Your drill was threatening
their settlement.

569
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,880
Now, the creature in the crypt.

570
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:58,080
Her name's Alaya.

571
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:02,520
She's one of their warriors,
and she's my best bargaining chip.

572
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:06,800
I need her alive. If she lives,
so do Elliot and Mo and Amy.

573
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:09,200
Because I will find them.

574
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:15,640
While I'm gone,

575
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:22,680
you four people, in this church,
in this corner of Planet Earth,

576
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:26,000
you have to be the best of humanity.

577
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:29,240
And what if they come back?
Shouldn't we be examining this creature,

578
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:32,160
dissecting it, finding its weak points?

579
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:34,240
No dissecting! No examining!
We return their hostage,

580
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:36,200
they return ours. Nobody gets harmed.

581
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:38,080
We can land this, together...

582
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:41,000
if you are the best you can be.

583
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:48,680
You are decent,

584
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:51,920
brilliant people.

585
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:54,760
Nobody dies today.

586
00:36:58,120 --> 00:36:59,320
Understand?

587
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:14,760
No, sorry, no, what are you doing?

588
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:18,160
Coming with you, of course!
What is it, some kind of...transport pod?

589
00:37:18,240 --> 00:37:21,360
Sort of, but you're not...
coming with me.

590
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:23,000
He's right, you're not.

591
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:26,280
I have spent all my life excavating
the layers of this planet.

592
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:30,040
And now you want me to stand back while
you head down into it? I don't think so!

593
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:32,320
- I don't have time to argue!
- I thought we were in a rush.

594
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:35,160
- It'll be dangerous.
- Oh, so's crossing the road.

595
00:37:35,240 --> 00:37:37,800
Oh, for goodness' sake,
all right, then! Come on!

596
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:44,360
- Hey... Come back safe.
- Of course.

597
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:54,160
Welcome aboard the TARDIS.
Now, don't touch anything.

598
00:37:54,240 --> 00:37:56,640
- Very precious.
- No way!

599
00:37:58,040 --> 00:38:00,160
But...but that's...

600
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:02,840
This is...

601
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:06,880
...fantastic!

602
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:09,520
- What does it do?
- Everything!

603
00:38:09,600 --> 00:38:11,840
I'm hoping, if we're going down,

604
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:14,040
- that barricade won't inter...fere!
- (CRASHING)

605
00:38:14,120 --> 00:38:16,920
- Did you touch something?!
- No! Isn't this what it does?!

606
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:20,440
I'm not doing anything!
We've been hijacked, I can't stop it!

607
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:23,800
They must've sensed
the electromagnetic field!

608
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:32,000
They're pulling the TARDIS
down into the Earth!

609
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:37,560
You had to come and see me.

610
00:38:37,640 --> 00:38:40,640
We...are going to keep you safe.

611
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:46,560
Your tribe are going to give us back
our people, in exchange for you.

612
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:48,360
No.

613
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:57,120
Shall I tell you what's
really going to happen, apes?

614
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:59,440
One of you will kill me.

615
00:39:00,520 --> 00:39:02,720
My death shall ignite a war.

616
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:07,240
And every stinking ape shall be wiped
from the surface of my beloved planet.

617
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:09,080
We won't allow that to happen.

618
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:11,600
I know apes better
than you know yourselves.

619
00:39:13,160 --> 00:39:16,320
I know which one of you will kill me.

620
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:17,760
Do you?

621
00:39:21,680 --> 00:39:23,680
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

622
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:46,840
Whoa! Whoa!

623
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:53,720
(RUMBLING SUBSIDES)

624
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:57,200
- Oi.
- Where are we?

625
00:40:04,400 --> 00:40:06,280
(LOOSE EARTH FALLS)

626
00:40:08,640 --> 00:40:10,000
Oh!

627
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:12,560
- (HE WHISTLES)
- (ECHO)

628
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:15,920
Looks like we fell through the bottom
of their tunnel system.

629
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:18,680
Don't suppose it was designed
for handling something like this.

630
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:23,080
- How far down are we?
- Oh...a lot more than 21 km.

631
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:25,880
So why aren't we burning alive?

632
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:27,680
Don't know.

633
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:29,360
Interesting, isn't it?

634
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:33,880
- It's like this is every day to you!
- Not every day.

635
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:35,200
Every other day.

636
00:40:58,600 --> 00:41:00,640
Don't struggle.

637
00:41:00,720 --> 00:41:03,280
(WHISPERING) Close your eyes
and don't struggle.

638
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:05,560
What? Where am I?

639
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:09,040
- Why can't I move my body?
- Decontamination, they call it.

640
00:41:10,680 --> 00:41:13,160
They did it to me. While I was conscious.

641
00:41:13,240 --> 00:41:16,760
OK, you're freaking me out now.
Did what? Who did?

642
00:41:16,840 --> 00:41:18,920
Dissected me.

643
00:41:22,800 --> 00:41:24,680
No...

644
00:41:26,520 --> 00:41:28,280
He's coming!

645
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:30,680
I'm sorry, I...

646
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:33,120
I wish I could help you!

647
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:44,200
We're looking for
a small tribal settlement.

648
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:48,480
Probably housing around...
a dozen Homo reptilia.

649
00:41:48,560 --> 00:41:50,160
Maybe less.

650
00:41:51,200 --> 00:41:55,120
- One...small tribe?
- Yeah.

651
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:56,760
Maybe a...dozen?

652
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:09,160
Ah.

653
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:13,680
Maybe more than a dozen.

654
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:16,600
Maybe more like an entire civilisation

655
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:18,320
living beneath the earth.

